.TH PGMMOUNTAINS 1 "April 5, 1998"
.SH NAME \"{{{roff}}}\"{{{
pgmmountains \- generate a random landscape of mountains and sea
.\"}}}
.SH SYNOPSIS \"{{{
.ad l
.B pgmmountains
.ad b
.\"}}}
.SH DESCRIPTION \"{{{
pgmmountains generates a random landscape of mountains and sea on standard
output.  The algorithm starts with a single triangle, which is divided
in four triangles.  The corners of these triangles are modified using
random numbers.  Each of these triangles is again splitted.  If corners
fall below heigth zero, they will be painted as sea.
.\"}}}
.SH AUTHOR \"{{{
Michael Haardt, 1998.
.\"}}}
.SH HISTORY \"{{{
The algorithm used is a slightly modified version of the algorithm
presented in \(lqFrank/Kreuder, Norbert Siepenkötter: \fIGebirge aus dem Computer\fP, Amiga-Magazin
10/1987, p. 83\(rq.
.\"}}}
